#originalTopic=should-the-us-have-universal-healthcare
Let's think about this one.  Under the system that we currently have, the people decide what is best. Collectively.  Apparently, 56% of voters here desire universal health care. This is a huge issue nationwide.  The state that we elect exists to serve the needs and desires of the people... not to promote capitalism.   And, if capitalism didn't interfere with government as much as government does capitalism, it would have happened long ago. 